INSERT INTO `activity_log` VALUES (1,'default','updated',16,'App\\Models\\Project\\ProjectInformation',1,'App\\User','{\"attributes\":{\"project_id\":16,\"sponsor_id\":1,\"ocid\":\"ocds-aaaaaa-16\",\"stage_id\":1,\"project_need\":\"<p>The need of the Project emanates from the following; a) the capacity of the existing hostels is very low&nbsp;compared with the demand (1,200 of 6,068 students gets accommodation, which translates to an absorption&nbsp;capacity of just 20%); b) the LGTI has limited financial capability to execute the Project on its own through&nbsp;the public procurement route as the estimated capital expenditure (capex) for the Project is TZS 12,726&nbsp;million (excluding interest during construction) while the cash balance available with the LGTI at the end of&nbsp;fiscal 2018 was only TZS 148 million; c) the students living in the private hostels are exposed to unfavorable&nbsp;and unhygienic living conditions, which adversely affects their health and education leading to low grades&nbsp;and pass rates; and d) the students, particularly females, are exposed to major safety and security issues&nbsp;due to travelling alone to and from the institute and minimal or no security measures at these hostels.<\\/p>\",\"description_services\":\"<p>Since education is a social and public good, its knock-on effects have a profound impact on the society at&nbsp;large, both in the short and long term. Similarly, the Project would benefit the students in various ways such&nbsp;as: a) improved grades and pass rates; b) savings in costs related to rent, healthcare and transportation; c)&nbsp;improved employability and earning potential; d) safety and security; e) saving in travel time, which can be&nbsp;utilized for productive activities; and f) easier access to educational facilities along with peer learning.<\\/p>\",\"reasons_ppp\":\"<p>Given the need to combine both the construction and operation in one contract, and considering the LGTI&rsquo;s&nbsp;limited financing ability, we recommend a design, build, finance, operate, maintain, and transfer (DBFOMT)&nbsp;model. This optimizes the ProjectCo&rsquo;s incentives structure and minimizes the lifecycle costs of&nbsp; construction&nbsp;and operation. Further, we have provided an illustrative set of input and output specifications that the&nbsp;ProjectCo will be expected to fulfill under the PPP agreement for the Project in addition to a set of&nbsp;performance standards on which the performance of the ProjectCo would be evaluated during the course of&nbsp;the Project.<\\/p>\",\"stakeholder_consultation\":null,\"description_asset\":\"<p>The hostel buildings will have 640 four-student rooms, and will be able to accommodate 2,560 students. This&nbsp;will improve the students&rsquo; absorption capacity from 20% to 62% of the enrolled students (including the&nbsp;existing capacity of 1,200 student and additional capacity of 2,560 students the Project is expected to&nbsp;create). The estimated capex of the Project is TZS 12,726 million (excluding interest during construction), of&nbsp;which construction cost of the hostel buildings is TZS 11,830 million (93% of the total capex) and the cost of&nbsp;room furniture is TZS 897 million (7% of the total capex).<\\/p>\",\"project_summary_document\":\"Pre-feasibility study report\",\"project_value_usd\":5.46,\"project_value_second\":12726,\"ppp_delivery_model_id\":1},\"old\":{\"project_id\":16,\"sponsor_id\":9,\"ocid\":\"ocds-aaaaaa-16\",\"stage_id\":1,\"project_need\":\"<p>The need of the Project emanates from the following; a) the capacity of the existing hostels is very low&nbsp;compared with the demand (1,200 of 6,068 students gets accommodation, which translates to an absorption&nbsp;capacity of just 20%); b) the LGTI has limited financial capability to execute the Project on its own through&nbsp;the public procurement route as the estimated capital expenditure (capex) for the Project is TZS 12,726&nbsp;million (excluding interest dur