te and again the Authority would be dependent on the third-party marketing agents. The project business is dynamic in nature and subject to frequent changes which warrant instant responses to market dynamics wherein there could be certain limitations for the Authority. In absence of a robust mechanism to optimize the revenues, it would be extremely difficult to create a sustainable template for the project vision\\u2013 to develop Zanzibar into a world class MICE destination. In light of the above facts and foregoing discussions, it is recommended that the project may be implemented through the DBFOM (user pay) model wherein the Concessionaire assumes the revenue risk, is provided with the freedom, flexibility and motivation to develop, operate and generate rate of return to recover the project lifecycle costs. The Authority shall create an enabling environment for successful development of the project that shall be attractive for the investors.\",\"stakeholder_consultation\":\"\",\"description_asset\":\"The various facilities proposed within the ITCC include one Convention Centre with two floors, Five exhibition halls of single floors, a hotel block with three floors, office building  with three floors, one stop centre with two floors, a medical centre with a single floor, club and amenities with two floors and two apartment buildings with five floors each.\",\"project_summary_document\":\"\",\"project_value_usd\":44,\"project_value_second\":105662,\"ppp_delivery_model_id\":2},\"old\":{\"project_id\":35,\"sponsor_id\":4,\"ocid\":\"ocds-aaaaaa-35\",\"stage_id\":1,\"project_need\":\"Established in the Fumba Economic Zone, the International Trade and Conventional Centre is a flagship project strategically created to optimize the tourism opportunity of the isles for regional and international events. The project objective is realized through a modern international trade and convention centre (ITCC) that will be at par with world standards and attractive to the dynamic 